      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/2/191/1",
      "text": [
        ": یَا ابْنَ عَمَّارٍ لَا تَدَعْ قِرَاءَهَ سُورَهِ تَبارَکَ الَّذِی نَزَّلَ الْفُرْقانَ عَلی عَبْدِهِ فَإِنَّ مَنْ قَرَأَهَا فِی کُلِّ لَیْلَهٍ لَمْ یُعَذِّبْهُ اللَّهُ أَبَداً وَ لَمْ یُحَاسِبْهُ وَ کَانَ مَنْزِلُهُ فِی الْفِرْدَوْسِ الْأَعْلَی."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "1. From the previous chain from al-Hassan from Sayf b. ’Umayra from Ishaq b. Ammar from Abi al-Hassan (a.s.) who said: “O Ibne Ammar! Do not avoid recitation of Tabaarakalladhee nazzalal furqaana a’laa a’bdihi. One who recites it every night, Allah will never chastise him and not take his account and his abode will be in the high garden of Paradise.”"
        ]
      }
